Export data from Jira into a CSV file suitable for ingestion by the See Scrum application.   This is a first step toward automated integration via web service.

Follow these step which created the attached csv:

# select Issues in left hand Nav
# select Advanced Search on right near Top
# select Switch to JQL link at right of the query fields
# Verify that the JQL displays all fields like this:  project = "SS" ORDER BY created DESC
# Select Export at Top right
# Select Export XML 
# Right click in Chrome to Save file as jira.xml
# Upload xml file to [https://www.freeformatter.com/xml-to-json-converter.html#ad-output|https://www.freeformatter.com/xml-to-json-converter.html#ad-output] 
# Press convert to json
# scroll down and press Copy to Clipboard and save in a new json file

fields.description:
* Create a Git project to maintain the source code for See Scrum.  
* Back up See Scrum project
* Validate that development and pull request round trip works for the web project
* Add the python server to the git repo
* Rename ScrumSee to SeeScrum 
* Merge develop branch into master after a full test

*GET LATEST*
git checkout develop
git fetch origin
git pull origin develop

*MAKE A CHANGE*
git branch my-chart
git checkout my-chart
git status
Develop changes

*CHECK IN THE CHANGE*
git add .
git commit -m 'feat: my chart'
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git merge --no-ff my-chart
git push origin develop

*DISCARD LOCAL CHANGES*

{noformat}git fetch --all
git reset --hard origin/develop{noformat}

*Merge develop BRANCH TO master*

{noformat}(on branch development)$ git merge master
(resolve any merge conflicts if there are any)
git checkout master 
git merge development
git push -u origin master{noformat}

*Set Git Config Info*

{noformat}$ git config --global user.email "you@example.com" 
$ git config --global user.name "Your Name"

$ git config --list    # see if the 'name' & 'email' are set correctly{noformat}

Developer’s API:  [https://developer.github.com/v3/|https://developer.github.com/v3/]

*Authentication*

* curl -u jamesmassa [https://api.github.com/user|https://api.github.com/user] 
* enter password at prompt

*Get Data*

* Make repo public
* Get the repo curl [https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee|https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee]
* Inspect the repo for all relevant api endpoints
* curl [https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee/commits|https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee/commits] > ./data/commits.json
* curl [https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee/contributors|https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee/contributors] > ./data/contributors.json
* curl [https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee/languages|https://api.github.com/repos/jamesmassa/scrumsee/languages] > ./data/languages.json
* Make repo private again

* Sprint Metrics values (Backlog story count,  Sprint Planning IFAs, Sprint backlog story points, etc.)
